<item>
            <title>[LU-11763] Add warning to necessitate use of network interface to configure LNet from Lustre 2.13</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11763</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, a network interface in modparam.conf is not necessary to be provided to configure LNet using lctl command - &quot;lctl network configure&quot; or &quot;lctl network up&quot;. In this case, a default value (&quot;eth0&quot; for socklnd or &quot;ib0&quot; for o2iblnd) is used to configure network.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With the LNet sysfs implementation, a network interface is necessary to build the sysfs hierarchy. lnetctl utility already has this restriction. &lt;br/&gt;
 This is why it has been decided to impose this restriction with lctl utility as well. Adding a warning message stating this restriction before we implement it will help users to be aware of it beforehand.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
